Over 30,000 United Teachers of Los Angeles (UTLA) members walked off the job.
This steady and systematic deterioration has also made Los Angeles schools more segregated.
In Los Angeles, Democratic Mayor Eric Garcetti enjoys a city council comprised of 14 Democrats out of 15 seats.
Los Angeles Teachers Can Lead The WayTeachers from across the state and country are looking to Los Angeles teachers to lead the way in this struggle against privatization and for their students.
This is a fight not just for LA teachers, but for teachers across the state, for the working class of Los Angeles, the state of California, and beyond.